I'm a bit skeptical; Corbenic immortality seems to be in the same manner as End of Death, where people can be injured but remain alive regardless. Cain and Able have different types of immortality, however. Cain reflects all damage directed towards him, and Able has human-level durability but essentially respawns after dying.







